They were just sixteen when the people were mean
So they didn't love themselves, and now they're gone
Headstones on a lawn

And when I was younger, I knew a boy and a boy
Best friends with each other, but always wished they were more
'Cause they loved one another, but never discovered

Moved to different states

Oh, and I'm afraid that's just the way the world works
It ain't funny, it ain't pretty, it ain't sweet

But I think that it could work for you and me
Just wait and see
It's not the end of the story

But I think that it could work for you and me
Just wait and see

snippet.textDisplay:
i dont expect anyone to read this, but if you do thanks :).


first day of seventh grade. im one of the few girls in my pe period. girl comes up to me, and tells me were gonna be friends because i was one of the few girls in the class. fast-forward a few weeks, i end up having a crush on her. shes really flirty with everyone, and we have a small friend group in the period made up of 2 other girls.


one day, were on the floor in the gym and we dont have to do anything in pe. she tells everyone in the group that she has a crush on a girl. i said i didnt have a crush out of fear that shed ask me who and shed find out that it was her. she was just so pretty and out of my league.


after that day, i thought that she had to have a crush on me, right? she had my picture as her lock screen, and was hugging me and sitting with me in that period everyday. i had it really bad for her, and she was my first legitimate crush. i had no idea what to do, and i didnt want to tell anyone about it. i only ever told my best friend about it, up until yesterday.


eventually, the news gets out about who her crush is. turns out that its one of the other girls in our group, victoria.


obviously, my little gay heart shattered. i felt terrible, but didnt show it or tell anyone about it. my other inner turmoils about being gay, my fear of judgement, and school work piled on top of it and made me feel even worse.


she ended up transferring out of the pe class for a while, and we didnt really ever talk that much after that because she was kind of popular and had tons of friends and was always busy with them. eventually, she ended up transferring back in, and she seemed the same but different, and i started questioning my feelings for her. (i did still have a crush on her)


she transferred out of the district before eighth grade for reasons that i didnt know until i told 2 of my friends the whole story. apparently there were rumors going around that she had gotten pregnant and thats why she had to leave the district, which the girl that told me personally doesnt believe.


i dont know if i believe the rumors or not, but even so that doesnt change the way that i felt about her. 7th grade was a wild year, and i still think about her a lot. i dont know if i miss her or not now, though. its been a year and ive done a lot of reflecting. she could be toxic sometimes with her telling people that she wanted to kill herself, but she came from a bad family. she used to tackle everyone (not to the ground) even if they told her not to, and randomly punch people in the stomach or pinch their sides for no reason.


i think that im glad that shes gone. she caused me a lot of pain and questioning and wierd feelings. i never got to tell her how i felt, and i think that thats a good thing. 7th grade feels so surreal and like it never happened, but at the same time it feels like it was yesterday. im glad that its over now, though. i discovered a lot about myself that year. i tried cutting for the first time, (i dont do it now, and it was only a few times) i discovered how scared i am of other people, and i found out that i was gay, though at the time i thought i was pan or bi.


if you want to know what happened to victoria, she was a grade ahead of us and went to highschool this year. the other girl is still at school but we dont really talk anymore because she always overreacted about little things and would be toxic about it.


thanks if you read this, it really means a lot <333

if you want to know what happened to victoria, she was a grade ahead of us and went to highschool this year. the other girl is still at school but we dont really talk anymore because she always overreacted about little things and would be toxic about it.


thanks if you read this, it really means a lot <333

snippet.textDisplay:
parts of this song that hit hard/hit different:

"they were just 16, when the people were mean, so they didnt love themselves. and now theyre gone. headstones on a lawn."
"i knew a boy and a boy. bestfriends with each other, but always wished they were more. cuz they loved one another, but never discovered cuz they were too afraid of what they'd say. moved to different states. "
"oh and im afraid thats just the way the world works. it aint funny, it aint pretty, it aint sweet. oh and im afraid thats just the way the world works. but i think that it could work for you and me. just wait and see..... "
" its not the end of the story. "
"...onto the sequel. about me and my friend. both our parents were evil, so we both made a bet. if we worked and we saved we could both run away and we'd have a better life. and i was right. i wonder if she's alright.... "
"and the movie's always running in my head. all the people, all the lovers, all my friends ! and i hope that they all get their happy end. in the end....."
and also the last chorus, the part where it feels like thunder banging on a window after each word

in conclusion, this whole song is just a repeated punch in the gut.
snippet.textOriginal:
parts of this song that hit hard/hit different:

"they were just 16, when the people were mean, so they didnt love themselves. *and now theyre gone.* headstones on a lawn."
"i knew a boy and a boy. bestfriends with each other, but always wished they were more. cuz they loved one another, but never discovered *cuz they were too afraid of what they'd say. moved to different states.* "
"oh and *im afraid thats just the way the world works.* it aint funny, it aint pretty, it aint sweet. oh and im afraid thats just the way the world works. *but i think that it could work for you and me. just wait and see.....* "
" *its not the end of the story.* "
"...onto the sequel. about me and my friend. both our parents were evil, so we both made a bet. *if we worked and we saved we could both run away and we'd have a better life.* and i was right. *i wonder if she's alright....* "
"and the movie's always running in my head. all the people, all the lovers, *all my friends ! and i hope that they all get their happy end.* in the end....."
and also the last chorus, the part where it feels like thunder banging on a window after each word

in conclusion, this whole song is just a repeated punch in the gut.
